The program must accept a string S and an integer X as the input. The program must print the
X
th
character from the first and then print the Xth
character from the last in the string S as the output.
Boundary Condition(s):
1 <= Length of S <= 100
1 <= X <= Length of S
Input Format:
The first line contains the string S.
The second line contains the integer X.
Output Format:
The first line contains two characters.
Example Input/Output 1:
Input:
watermelon
3
Output:
tl
Example Input/Output 2:
Input:
umbrella
6
Output:
lb



Code :


import java.util.*;
public class Hello {

    public static void main(String[] args) {
		Scanner sc=new Scanner(System.in);
		String str=sc.next();
		int n=sc.nextInt();
		int len=str.length();
		System.out.print(str.charAt(n-1));
		System.out.print(str.charAt(len-n));
	}
}
